    • Constructor Detail

      • ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE

        public ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE()
        The default constructor builds an ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE with "autoSynch" turned off. This means that you cannot observe the fields from the Java side (it can only be passed into Allegro methods). This is good for performance, since normally the fields do not need to be observed.
